Great.

9
00:00:58,790 --> 00:01:02,112
I'm Allie Fisk, 22 Dearborn Street here in Medford.

10
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:11,880
I am the business and cultural liaison in the mayor's office and today I'm presenting on an application the mayor's office submitted for restoration to the Condon Shell.

11
00:01:12,761 --> 00:01:14,042
So just a little bit of background.

12
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:23,671
The Condon Shell is a concrete bandshell structure located on DCR Parkland between the Mystic River as well as Route 16 over near Whole Foods.

13
00:01:24,151 --> 00:01:30,136
It was constructed in 1956 and is a National Register of Historic Places nominee.

14
00:01:31,117 --> 00:01:34,961
Over the last three years, it has seen a tremendous increase in usage.

15
00:01:35,641 --> 00:01:39,625
Particularly in the last year, there were 50 events total that took place there.

16
00:01:39,645 --> 00:01:41,987
The farmers market now is there on a weekly basis.

17
00:01:42,447 --> 00:01:45,990
There are various festivals as well as a concert series that happen there.

18
00:01:46,511 --> 00:01:50,895
So there are about 10,000 people a year that are being served by the Condon Shelf.

19
00:01:52,336 --> 00:02:01,024
It's one of the Medford's most recognizable landmarks, and you can see it from Route 16, and it really represents Medford's dedication to arts and culture here in the city.

20
00:02:01,724 --> 00:02:12,634
The exterior, of course, is being used for concerts as well as festivals, and the interior currently is being used for storage for the Medford Farmers Market, which is taking place there every week now.

21
00:02:14,675 --> 00:02:18,799
And I wanted to talk a little bit about what the current conditions are and why I'm here today.

22
00:02:19,319 --> 00:02:23,262
So the Condon shell right now has a tremendous number of leaks.

23
00:02:23,322 --> 00:02:38,193
That's one of the primary issues is that the leaks not only of course get into the interior of the shell and can affect people's ability to store stuff there, it really can compromise the integrity of the masonry itself and over time is going to continue to wear on the masonry and become an issue.

24
00:02:38,693 --> 00:02:43,316
And it can also affect the electrical equipment in there if the water were to get in.

25
00:02:43,396 --> 00:02:45,157
So that is a primary concern right now.

26
00:02:46,137 --> 00:02:53,101
Also significant is the exterior of the shell has really seen a lot of wear and tear over the last 60 years.

27
00:02:53,521 --> 00:02:55,683
And we have all seen that it has a nice

28
00:02:56,583 --> 00:03:04,146
film of grime on it, and we'd really like to see it restored to its beautiful state that it was in in the 50s when it was originally built.

29
00:03:04,747 --> 00:03:07,308
And another concern about the space is that there's no lighting.

30
00:03:07,368 --> 00:03:14,591
Right now, there are two large lampposts that are directly in front of the shell that are not working, and there's no lighting behind the shell.

31
00:03:14,691 --> 00:03:24,355
So events that happen there in the evening, at this point, it's a safety concern that there's no lighting on the exterior of the shell when the farmer's market, for instance, loads in and unloads their equipment.

32
00:03:25,155 --> 00:03:27,516
So that's a big issue that we have as well.

33
00:03:28,016 --> 00:03:47,923
So the proposed work right now is pressure washing the exterior of the shell, cleaning, prepping, and sealing all of the cracks to fix the leaks, covering the entire exterior of the shell with a waterproof, water-resistant coating to prevent further wear, and then repairing existing lighting and installing new lighting to the exterior of the shell.

34
00:03:48,863 --> 00:04:03,239
So the Condon shell sits right now on DCR own property, but the city has a joint management and license agreement with this with DCR in order to be able to renovate the shell to make these restorations we do have their permission.

35
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:07,442
We also have checked in with the Massachusetts Historic Commission.

36
00:04:07,482 --> 00:04:13,825
They have ruled that this will have no adverse effects on the historic integrity of the facility.

37
00:04:14,225 --> 00:04:21,830
And I'm in communication with the Secretary of the Conservation Commission to ensure that the project won't have any environmental effects as well.

38
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:27,724
So the total estimate for the project is $111,520.

39
00:04:28,344 --> 00:04:36,992
This will cover the cost of labor, mobilization, as well as material costs for both the masonry of the shell as well as the electrical work.

40
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:40,035
So the amount being requested from the CPC is $80,265.

41
00:04:40,075 --> 00:04:41,316
That is 75% of the project cost.

42
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:51,061
The city will also be putting in in-kind donations for the electrical labor.

43
00:04:51,542 --> 00:04:56,183
It'll be city work, and we'll be covering the remaining 25% of the cost of the project.

44
00:04:57,804 --> 00:05:11,548
The quote was gathered through detailed conversations with a contractor who has experience with masonry, as well as is familiar with the shell, and we've also been working closely with the building department and the electrical department to make sure that our quote is very thorough.

45
00:05:13,107 --> 00:05:17,560
And DCR was approached to ask whether or not they had available funds for the project, and they do not.

46
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,385
So that is not a possibility at this time.

47
00:05:20,535 --> 00:05:26,081
Once the project begins, it will take about four weeks to complete, barring any weather concerns.

48
00:05:26,581 --> 00:05:32,147
We did originally, when we submitted the application, say that we were ready to commence the work in June of 2018.

49
00:05:32,407 --> 00:05:34,269
Of course, that would be next month.

50
00:05:34,749 --> 00:05:42,897
But given the timing, we now realize that that's going to impair too many of the events already scheduled to use the show and could displace many of them.

51
00:05:43,017 --> 00:05:44,579
So we feel it would be more appropriate

52
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:51,164
to begin the project in May of 2019 before the festival season and the concert season has begun.

53
00:05:53,025 --> 00:05:59,450
So in conclusion, I do feel like this project very closely aligns with the goals of the Community Preservation Act.

54
00:06:00,471 --> 00:06:09,958
Certainly when the plan was created and there were public meetings, the content shell came up on numerous occasions as being a project people really wanted to see potentially funded.

55
00:06:10,818 --> 00:06:22,404
And I know that it does fit into two of the funding categories, historic preservation, as well as open space and recreation, and really nails a couple of the boxes there when talking about those priorities.

56
00:06:23,144 --> 00:06:26,386
There's no question at all that this is a really valuable resource in the city.

57
00:06:26,446 --> 00:06:30,588
There are people here today who can say that as well, that they're using it on a regular basis.

58
00:06:30,928 --> 00:06:39,553
There's people here who likely remember it when it was first built, and we really want to see it restored to what it was at that time so it can be used for that purpose moving forward.

59
