1194
01:50:19,208 --> 01:50:23,631
We like our location because there's actually parking there.

1195
01:50:26,193 --> 01:50:29,975
Certainly, working with the library is an intriguing possibility.

1196
01:50:31,486 --> 01:50:33,628
We cooperate with them extensively.

1197
01:50:34,789 --> 01:50:40,912
We're kind of working out an understanding where certain kinds of records such as city records would reside there.

1198
01:50:41,473 --> 01:50:42,914
Other things would reside with us.

1199
01:50:46,036 --> 01:50:53,481
I really don't think the library would have a lot of time to spend figuring out how to do this given the schedule they're under.

1200
01:50:54,581 --> 01:50:56,102
We have thought about it from time to time.

1201
01:50:56,142 --> 01:50:56,983
We sort of like

1202
01:51:00,354 --> 01:51:03,496
Our meeting room seems to be about the right size.

1203
01:51:04,097 --> 01:51:09,320
It accommodates up to 40-45 people and that's our typical sort of audience.

1204
01:51:12,763 --> 01:51:19,048
There would be advantages, but I haven't found a really plausible way of doing that.

1205
01:51:20,535 --> 01:51:34,623
My second question is whether you have any base of deep-pocketed individual donors who could match if matching funds were provided.

1206
01:51:36,724 --> 01:51:38,265
What do you mean by deep-pocketed?

1207
01:51:39,746 --> 01:51:44,029
If you got half of the money for this, do you have people who could contribute the other half?

1208
01:51:44,089 --> 01:51:45,850
We do double handstands when we get $500.

1209
01:51:45,890 --> 01:51:46,550
Let me put it that way.

1210
01:51:50,869 --> 01:52:02,094
We did have one Bluebird donation of $20,000 a couple of years ago, which is what's really funding all the other improvements we're doing, such as the stucco repair.

1211
01:52:02,114 --> 01:52:11,339
Now that the stucco has been repaired, we have to repaint the building, improving the drainage around the building, things of that nature.

1212
01:52:17,320 --> 01:52:19,041
Any further questions, comments?

1213
01:52:19,441 --> 01:52:21,381
Can I just make a comment?

1214
01:52:21,422 --> 01:52:21,502
Yes.

1215
01:52:21,522 --> 01:52:27,124
Remember, we're building an average new library.

1216
01:52:27,164 --> 01:52:37,567
And we have literally, I was working with Barbara today, there's not going to be any space for 20,000 to 30,000 additional items, reading and research spaces, et cetera.

1217
01:52:37,807 --> 01:52:40,228
We are not building a library that is beyond average.

1218
01:52:40,388 --> 01:52:43,469
You heard that great speech by that gentleman the other night.

1219
01:52:45,761 --> 01:52:48,143
I'll be consulting with you on the color.

